## 2. Logo & Identity

### Primary Logo

The Invicta logo is loaded from Shopify theme settings (`settings.logo`) and rendered in the header via an `<img>` tag at a maximum width of 400px. The logo appears left-aligned in the header on desktop and centred between the hamburger menu and action icons on mobile.

If no logo image is uploaded, the theme falls back to the shop name rendered as an `h2` element with class `invicta-header__logo-text`.

### Favicon

The favicon is served from Shopify theme settings (`settings.favicon`) as a 32x32 PNG via the Shopify CDN `image_url` filter.

### Usage Rules

- Minimum clear space around the logo: equal to the height of the letter "I" in INVICTA on all sides.
- The logo must always appear on a white or very light background (`#f5f5f6` or lighter), or reversed out to white on the dark (`#2d2d2d`) background.
- Never place the logo on the red accent colour.
- Never rotate, stretch, add effects to, or recolour the logo beyond the approved mono/reversed variants.
- Never reduce the logo below 120px wide on screen or 30mm wide in print.

### Brand SVG Library

The following brand logos are available as SVG files in the `assets/` directory. All should be used as monochrome where possible to maintain visual consistency:

Bahco, CT1, DeWalt, Dormer, Einhell, Everbuild, Evo-Stik, Faithfull, Gorilla, HiKOKI, Irwin, Kamtec, Lamello, Makita, Metabo, Milwaukee, Paslode, Siroflex, SiteTuff, Soudal, Spit, Stanley, Starrett, TengTools, Timco.

