## 11. Channel Consistency

### Cross-Channel Standards

Shopify, Amazon FBM, and eBay listings share the same product descriptions and specifications. A product is a single commercial entity across all channels. Wording can be adapted for platform requirements, but the core content stays consistent.

### Titles

- SEO-optimised, under 60 characters.
- Format: Brand + Product Name + Key Spec. Example: "DeWalt DCD776 18V Combi Drill 2x 1.3Ah".
- No promotional text in titles ("BEST SELLER", "FREE DELIVERY", "SALE").

### Meta Descriptions

- Under 160 characters.
- Action verb opener. Delivery mention closer.
- Example: "Order the DeWalt DCD776 18V combi drill with 2x 1.3Ah batteries. In stock, next-day delivery available."

### Product Body Copy

- Trade-focused. Specs first, features second, marketing last.
- Lead with what the tradesperson needs to know: voltage, capacity, weight, compatibility.
- HTML body content in Shopify should use semantic headings and spec tables where appropriate.

