## 12. Accessibility Requirements

WCAG AA compliance is the minimum standard across all pages.

### Core Requirements

- All interactive elements: 44px minimum touch target (`--inv-touch-target-min`).
- All images: meaningful alt text. Not just the product title; describe what is shown.
- All form fields: associated `<label>` elements. No placeholder-only labels.
- Colour contrast: 4.5:1 minimum ratio for normal text, 3:1 minimum for large text (18px+ or 14px+ bold).
- `prefers-reduced-motion` must be respected on all animations. Every `@keyframes` or transition must have a corresponding `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` override.

### Focus States

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--inv-focus-ring-width` | `2px` | Focus ring thickness |
| `--inv-focus-ring-color` | `rgba(225, 29, 38, 0.5)` | Red-tinted focus ring |
| `--inv-focus-ring-offset` | `2px` | Gap between element and ring |
| `--inv-focus-shadow` | `0 0 0 3px rgba(45, 45, 45, 0.3)` | Alternative focus shadow |

- Every interactive element must have a visible focus indicator. The default is a 2px ring in `--inv-focus-ring-color` with 2px offset.
- Skip-to-content link is present in the theme and must be maintained.
- ARIA landmarks are used: `role="banner"` on header, `role="complementary"` on trust bar, `aria-label` on navigation.

